<h1>
  Your community group is growing, and you’re seeing your dreams become reality. Find out what’s best for your group in the future.
</h1>

<p class="lead">
  Running a community group takes ideas, heart and dedication. It also takes time, and probably money. When you’re making the world a better place in your spare time, there will come a point where there just aren’t enough hours in the day to do all the things you want to do.
</p>

<p>
  Becoming a charity, social enterprise or nonprofit means you could get funding to have more paid time for the great work you do in your community.
</p>

<p>
  But there are lots of different legal structures available to community groups, and finding the right approach for your group can be daunting.
</p>

<p>
  Thinking about getting a more official status for your group? This guide will help you decide for yourself what is the best direction to take your group in.
</p>

